        <header class="article-header">
            <h4 class="post-upperdek">
      Prime the money faucet    &mdash;
</h4>
            <h1 itemprop="headline">The best summer Prime Day deals we could find for Ars readers</h1>
            <h2 itemprop="description">On day two of Amazon's summer sale extravaganza, here are the deals we liked.</h2>
            <section class="post-meta">

  
<p class="byline" itemprop="author creator" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
      <a itemprop="url" href="https://arstechnica.com/author/lee-hutchinson/"  rel="author" ><span itemprop="name">Lee Hutchinson</span></a>
    -    <time class="date" data-time="1721221238" datetime="2024-07-17T13:00:38+00:00">Jul 17, 2024 1:00 pm UTC</time>
</p>

  
</section>        </header>
        <section class="article-guts">
            <div itemprop="articleBody" class="article-content post-page">
                                    
<figure class="intro-image intro-left">
  <img src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GettyImages-2161663985-800x534.jpg" alt="A close-up of several Amazon-branded boxes in a stacked pile">
      <figcaption class="caption"><div class="caption-text"><a href="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GettyImages-2161663985-scaled.jpg" class="enlarge-link" data-height="1707" data-width="2560">Enlarge</a> <span class="sep">/</span> It's Prime Day—again—which means a whole bunch of these boxes.</div><div class="caption-credit">NurPhoto / Getty Images</div></figcaption>  </figure>

